    <h1 class="title is-2 has-text-centered">About Whether Weather</h1>

    <p>
      Whether Weather is a client-side, privacy-focused weather dashboard.  No accounts or back-ends—just static HTML, CSS, and JavaScript running entirely in your browser.
    </p>

    <h2 class="title is-4 mt-5">Features</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Dashboard: At-a-glance min/max + icon for six cities.</li>
      <li>City Focus: Hourly & 7-day forecasts with interactive cards.</li>
      <li>Favorites & Home City: Highlight your top picks and jump straight to them.</li>
      <li>Units & Dark Mode: Switch °C/°F, light/dark themes, and auto-refresh.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="title is-4 mt-5">Data & Icons</h2>
    <p>
      All weather data from the <a href="https://open-meteo.com/">Open-Meteo API</a>,  
      icons from <a href="https://openweathermap.org/">OpenWeatherMap</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="title is-4 mt-5">FAQ</h2>
    <p><strong>Why no signup?</strong> Preferences live in your browser’s localStorage, so there’s no server or account to maintain.</p>
    <p><strong>How often does data refresh?</strong> Based on your auto-refresh setting (5/15/30 min) or manually by reloading the page.</p>

